cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of nuclei segmentation in microscopy images using learning-based methods. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel learning strategy that boosts segmentation accuracy, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates different segmentation algorithms, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
